Aristarchus my fellowprisoner saluteth you, and Marcus, sister's son to Barnabas, (touching whom ye received commandments: if he come unto you, receive him;) }{\cs25\fs16\insrsid8935864\charrsid8935864 11}{\insrsid8935864 
 And Jesus, which is called Justus, who are of the circumcision. These only are my fellowworkers unto the kingdom of God, which have been a comfort unto me. }{\cs25\fs16\insrsid8935864\charrsid8935864 12}{\insrsid8935864 
 Epaphras, who is one of you, a servant of Christ, saluteth you, always labouring fervently for you in prayers, that ye may stand perfect and complete in all the will of God. }{\cs25\fs16\insrsid8935864\charrsid8935864 13}{\insrsid8935864 
 For I bear him record, that he hath a great zeal for you, and them that are in Laodicea, and them in Hierapolis. }{\cs25\fs16\insrsid8935864\charrsid8935864 14}{\insrsid8935864  Luke, the beloved physician, and Demas, greet you. }{
\cs25\fs16\insrsid8935864\charrsid8935864 15}{\insrsid8935864  Salute the brethren which are in Laodicea, and Nymphas, and the church which is in his house. }{\cs25\fs16\insrsid8935864\charrsid8935864 16}{\insrsid8935864 
 And when this epistle is read among you, cause that it be read also in the church of the Laodiceans; and that ye likewise read the epistle from Laodicea. }{\cs25\fs16\insrsid8935864\charrsid8935864 17}{\insrsid8935864  }{\insrsid8935864\charrsid8935864 
And}{\insrsid8935864  say to Archippus, Take heed to the ministry which thou hast received in the Lord, that thou fulfil it. }{\cs25\fs16\insrsid8935864\charrsid8935864 18}{\insrsid8935864 
 The salutation by the hand of me Paul. Remember my bonds. Grace be with you. Amen.
\par 
\par }{\cs27\b\ul\insrsid8935864\charrsid8935864 Luke 10:1-15}{\insrsid8935864  }{\insrsid8935864 After these things the LORD appointed other seventy also, and sent them two and two before his face into every city and place, whither he himself would come. }{
\cs25\fs16\insrsid8935864\charrsid8935864 2}{\insrsid8935864  Therefore said he unto them, The harvest truly is great, but the labourers are few: pray ye therefore the Lord of the harvest, that he would send forth labourers into his harvest. }{
\cs25\fs16\insrsid8935864\charrsid8935864 3}{\insrsid8935864  Go your ways: behold, I send you forth as lambs among wolves. }{\cs25\fs16\insrsid8935864\charrsid8935864 4}{\insrsid8935864 
 Carry neither purse, nor scrip, nor shoes: and salute no man by the way. }{\cs25\fs16\insrsid8935864\charrsid8935864 5}{\insrsid8935864  And into whatsoever house ye enter, first say, Peace be to this house. }{\cs25\fs16\insrsid8935864\charrsid8935864 6}
{\insrsid8935864  And if the son of peace be there, your peace shall rest upon it: if not, it shall turn to you again. }{\cs25\fs16\insrsid8935864\charrsid8935864 7}{\insrsid8935864 
 And in the same house remain, eating and drinking such things as they give: for the labourer is worthy of his hire. Go not from house to house. }{\cs25\fs16\insrsid8935864\charrsid8935864 8}{\insrsid8935864 
 And into whatsoever city ye enter, and they receive you, eat such things as are set before you: }{\cs25\fs16\insrsid8935864\charrsid8935864 9}{\insrsid8935864 
 And heal the sick that are therein, and say unto them, The kingdom of God is come nigh unto you. }{\cs25\fs16\insrsid8935864\charrsid8935864 10}{\insrsid8935864 
 But into whatsoever city ye enter, and they receive you not, go your ways out into the streets of the same, and say, }{\cs25\fs16\insrsid8935864\charrsid8935864 11}{\insrsid8935864  Even the very dust 
of your city, which cleaveth on us, we do wipe off against you: notwithstanding be ye sure of this, that the kingdom of God is come nigh unto you. }{\cs25\fs16\insrsid8935864\charrsid8935864 12}{\insrsid8935864 
 But I say unto you, that it shall be more tolerable in that day for Sodom, than for that city. }{\cs25\fs16\insrsid8935864\charrsid8935864 13}{\insrsid8935864  Woe unto
 thee, Chorazin! woe unto thee, Bethsaida! for if the mighty works had been done in Tyre and Sidon, which have been done in you, they had a great while ago repented, sitting in sackcloth and ashes. }{\cs25\fs16\insrsid8935864\charrsid8935864 14}{
\insrsid8935864  }{\insrsid8935864\charrsid8935864 But}{\insrsid8935864  it shall be more tolerable for Tyre and Sidon at the judgment, than for you. }{\cs25\fs16\insrsid8935864\charrsid8935864 15}{\insrsid8935864 
 And thou, Capernaum, which art exalted to heaven, shalt be thrust down to hell.
\par }\pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid2974322 \fs24\lang1033\langfe255\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af34\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp255 {\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\dbch\af0\langfenp1033\insrsid10044948 
