\hich\af1\dbch\af34\loch\f1 ome.}{\cs26\f1\fs28\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\insrsid1998693 \hich\af1\dbch\af34\loch\f1  }{\cs26\f1\fs28\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\insrsid8935864\charrsid8935864 
\par }\pard\plain \s28\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid9181170 \fs28\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid8935864 
\par The sending of the 70 disciples was prophesied in the OT: 
\par 
\par }\pard \s28\qj \li720\ri720\widctlpar\faauto\rin720\lin720\itap0\pararsid12063128 {\insrsid8935864 \'93}{\insrsid8935864\charrsid8935864 
And they came to Elim, where were twelve wells of water, and threescore and ten palm trees: and they encamped there by the waters.}{\insrsid8935864 \'94 }{\cs25\f1\fs16\insrsid8935864\charrsid12063128 (Exo 15:27)}{\insrsid8935864\charrsid8935864   }{
\insrsid10044948 
\par }\pard \s28\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid8935864 {\insrsid5855982 
\par }{\insrsid8935864 The 12 and the 70 foreshadow the 12 and the 70 apostles. }{\insrsid12063128 Note how the 12 Apostles are wells (or fountains) of water, which in turn nourish the 70 palm trees. The teaching of the Apostles is preeminent
, and feeds their disciples, and the entire church. }{\insrsid1998693 It is fully appropriate that these fountains and palm trees were found at }{\i\insrsid1998693\charrsid1998693 \'93Elim\'94}{\insrsid1998693 , which interpreted means \'93ascent\'94. }{
\insrsid12063128 The fruit of the palm tree fully describes the teaching of the church, because, as Blessed Theophylact points out, the fruit is \'93sweet, yet tempered with astringency\'94 }{\cs25\f1\fs16\insrsid12063128\charrsid12063128 
(Commentary of Luke 10:1-3)}{\insrsid12063128  This same idea is expressed when the Good Samaritan, our Savior, poured into the wounds of the traveler }{\i\insrsid12063128\charrsid12063128 oil and wine}{\insrsid12063128 .}{\cs31\super\insrsid12063128 
\chftn {\footnote \pard\plain \s30\ql \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs20\lang1033\langfe255\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af34\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp255 {\cs31\super\insrsid12063128 \chftn }{\insrsid12063128 \hich\af0\dbch\af34\loch\f0  }{
\insrsid12063128\charrsid12063128 \hich\af0\dbch\af34\loch\f0 Luk}{\insrsid12063128 \hich\af0\dbch\af34\loch\f0 e}{\insrsid12063128\charrsid12063128 \hich\af0\dbch\af34\loch\f0 
 10:33-34  But a certain Samaritan, as he journeyed, came where he was: and when he saw him, he had compassion on him,  (34)  And went to him, and bound up his wounds, pouring in oil and wine, and set him on his own beast, and brought him to an inn, and
\hich\af0\dbch\af34\loch\f0  took care of him.}}}{\insrsid3551803  }{\insrsid1998693 Any true Christian teaching will have these qualities. We need to be encouraged and rebuked
, many times at the same moment in time. The oil soothes us, and without it we would lose heart, but the wine cleanses us, and without it, our wounds, caused by our passions and sins, would fester and we would die.  }{\insrsid8418824 
\par 
\par }{\insrsid8935864 We know }{\insrsid1998693 these things about this passage}{\insrsid8935864  because it is part of the mind of the church. Correct biblical }{\insrsid8418824 exegesis}{\insrsid8935864 
 is not possible unless we share the mind of the church. This is obtained not only by }{\insrsid8418824 reading}{\insrsid8935864  the commentaries of the holy fathers (the meaning of this }{\insrsid1998693 passage}{\insrsid8935864 
, for instance is expounded in Blessed Theophylact), but }{\insrsid8418824 also}{\insrsid8935864  especially }{\insrsid8418824 by}{\insrsid8935864  living the life of the church, and worshipping in an Orthodox manner. }{\insrsid8418824 
\par 
\par }{\insrsid8935864 The scriptures are continually interpreted in our services, especially in the matins service, and its canons. We can learn the inner meaning of the scriptures if we think and live }{\i\insrsid8935864\charrsid8418824 liturgically}{
\insrsid8935864 . The word \'93liturgy\'94 means \'93the work of the people\'94. It is not only a Sunday morning service}{\insrsid8418824 
, but the whole of our life. It is a terrible shame that we moderns have become by and large a non-liturgical people, with the liturgy confined to less than two hours on Sunday, instead of including daily perusal of the Holy Scriptures, fa
sting, standing in the other services in worship, with intent to learn of the things of God. 
\par 
\par I have stated before and do so again that the most important two hours of the entire week is the matins service on Saturday evening. In it we take time out to stop all other distractions of life, and try to learn of the things of God}{\insrsid11226764 
, where the scriptures, the commandments and the way of life is expounded. }{\insrsid8418824 . The Divine }{\insrsid11226764 Liturgy}{\insrsid8418824  is the center of our liturgical life, but it cannot be fully }{\insrsid11226764 appreciated}{
\insrsid8418824  or understood without the entirety of our life being liturgical. If we wish to understand the scriptures, we must not only read them, but also worship }{\i\insrsid8418824\charrsid11226764 with}{\insrsid8418824  them and follow them. }{
\insrsid8935864 
\par }{\insrsid11226764 
\par }{\cs27\b\f1\ul\insrsid3677618\charrsid10047888 Luke 10:5}{\insrsid3677618  }{\cs26\f1\insrsid3677618\charrsid10047888 And into whatsoever house ye enter, first say, Peace be to this house. 6
 And if the son of peace be there, your peace shall rest upon it: if not, it shall turn to you again.
\par }{\insrsid3677618 
\par For many years this verse was a puzzle to me. How can our peace return to us again? Now after many years, it is clear: in all things we should bless and be bringers of peace. This describes a way of life, an attitude which we should bri
ng to every encounter. There is no trace of cynicism in this way of life, and neither is there simple mindedness. We are to be \'93harmless as doves and wise as serpents\'94.}{\cs31\super\insrsid3677618 \chftn {\footnote \pard\plain 
\s30\ql \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs20\lang1033\langfe255\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af34\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp255 {\cs31\super\insrsid3677618 \chftn }{\insrsid3677618 \hich\af0\dbch\af34\loch\f0  }{\insrsid3677618\charrsid3677618 
\hich\af0\dbch\af34\loch\f0 Mat 10:16  Behold, I send you forth as sheep in the midst of wolves: be ye therefore wise as serpents, and harmless as doves.}}}{\insrsid3677618  
\par 
\par This passage tells us that we will never lose our peace, no matter how it is received. We must, give the \'93benefit of the doubt\'94 to every man, in every situation. 
If our teaching, or help is rejected, our peace returns to us, and we are no poorer, but only if our efforts were accomplished in the spirit of peace. I have learned the hard way that nothing in my ministry has ever been successful unless I first said 
\'93Peace be to this house\'94, and then proceeded. 
\par 
